WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.810 --> 00:00:02.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello.

00:00:02.610 --> 00:00:04.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm Chantal Westerman.

00:00:04.170 --> 00:00:06.460 align:middle line:84%
One of the best parts of
"The Wisdom Workshops"

00:00:06.460 --> 00:00:08.700 align:middle line:84%
are the up close and
personal conversations

00:00:08.700 --> 00:00:10.800 align:middle line:84%
with the leading
practitioners and authors

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:12.420 align:middle line:90%
in the holistic field.

00:00:12.420 --> 00:00:14.700 align:middle line:84%
This gives all of
us an opportunity

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:16.920 align:middle line:84%
to know these people
just a little bit better.

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:21.446 align:middle line:84%
So join me as they share
their wisdom with us.

00:00:21.446 --> 00:00:23.911 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:23.911 --> 00:00:50.550 align:middle line:90%


00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:53.520 align:middle line:10%
Nick, having read both your
books, particularly your most

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:57.720 align:middle line:10%
recent one, "In God's
Truth," it occurs to me

00:00:57.720 --> 00:01:03.750 align:middle line:10%
that the messages of, I guess
it would be 2,000 years ago,

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:06.930 align:middle line:10%
are the same messages
that we're hearing today.

00:01:06.930 --> 00:01:07.870 align:middle line:90%
Is that true?

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:09.330 align:middle line:90%
>> That is true.

00:01:09.330 --> 00:01:12.170 align:middle line:84%
In my case, that's a
commitment I've made.

00:01:12.170 --> 00:01:15.380 align:middle line:10%
In the 4th century AD the
messages of Jesus and Paul

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:17.550 align:middle line:10%
of 2,000 years ago
were distorted.

00:01:17.550 --> 00:01:20.280 align:middle line:10%
Messages of love were
changed to messages of fear.

00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:23.083 align:middle line:10%
Messages of compassion were
changed to messages of guilt.

00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:25.250 align:middle line:84%
And messages that were
supposed to bring us together

00:01:25.250 --> 00:01:27.505 align:middle line:84%
in brotherly and sisterly
love, [INAUDIBLE]

00:01:27.505 --> 00:01:29.940 align:middle line:84%
were unfortunately changed,
which, in many cases,

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:33.390 align:middle line:84%
polarized people, and created
prejudice and bigotry.

00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And today we're bringing
those messages back again.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.800 align:middle line:90%
>> What is it that allowed us?

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:39.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, gratefully,
they're back.

00:01:39.630 --> 00:01:44.810 align:middle line:84%
Because compassion and love
are so universally important.

00:01:44.810 --> 00:01:45.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:45.630 --> 00:01:46.942 align:middle line:90%
>> But what changed?

00:01:46.942 --> 00:01:48.900 align:middle line:84%
What is changing, I should
say, because I don't

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:50.150 align:middle line:90%
think it's changed completely.

00:01:50.150 --> 00:01:51.720 align:middle line:90%
But there's a shift.

00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.642 align:middle line:84%
>> I believe there's a spiritual
consciousness that is spreading

00:01:54.642 --> 00:01:56.100 align:middle line:84%
throughout the
United States today,

00:01:56.100 --> 00:01:57.690 align:middle line:84%
as well as the
rest of the world,

00:01:57.690 --> 00:02:00.210 align:middle line:84%
like never before in
the history of mankind.

00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:03.570 align:middle line:84%
Our minds are the gateways
to our hearts and soul.

00:02:03.570 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:84%
And more and more people
have opened up those gates,

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:08.460 align:middle line:84%
allowing information to come
into the hearts and souls

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:12.040 align:middle line:84%
that four or five years ago
they couldn't have done.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:15.870 align:middle line:84%
>> "The Messengers"
was wildly successful.

00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:20.250 align:middle line:84%
If you had written that book,
let's say, 10 years ago, would

00:02:20.250 --> 00:02:21.620 align:middle line:90%
it have been as successful.

00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:22.420 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:02:22.420 --> 00:02:24.160 align:middle line:90%
Not even five years ago.

00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:27.690 align:middle line:84%
And you can just see this in the
makeup of the audiences, where

00:02:27.690 --> 00:02:29.220 align:middle line:84%
six or seven years
ago the audience

00:02:29.220 --> 00:02:30.932 align:middle line:90%
would almost all be female.

00:02:30.932 --> 00:02:33.390 align:middle line:84%
It would have been more what
we would describe as a new age

00:02:33.390 --> 00:02:34.190 align:middle line:90%
audience.

00:02:34.190 --> 00:02:36.930 align:middle line:84%
But today it's a
cross-section of America.

00:02:36.930 --> 00:02:40.200 align:middle line:84%
We have people not only
of the different genders,

00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:42.060 align:middle line:84%
but from the different
walks of life.

00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:44.940 align:middle line:84%
I believe the bridge between
mainstream and new age

00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:49.320 align:middle line:84%
is so small now that you
can't even distinguish it.

00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:54.900 align:middle line:84%
>> "In God's Truth" paints a
very interesting image of God.

00:02:54.900 --> 00:02:58.960 align:middle line:84%
Because we all tend to have
a particular image of him.

00:02:58.960 --> 00:02:59.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:59.760 --> 00:03:04.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Kind of fire and brimstone
in some people's eyes.

00:03:04.710 --> 00:03:06.780 align:middle line:90%
>> You talk about who is God.

00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, in
traditional religion,

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.740 align:middle line:84%
coming from the Old Testament,
Isaiah described God

00:03:11.740 --> 00:03:15.240 align:middle line:84%
as an elderly man with a white
beard, and long white hair,

00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:18.690 align:middle line:84%
with a gown, with a long
robe sitting on a throne.

00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:21.060 align:middle line:10%
But what if God
didn't have a beard?

00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:23.280 align:middle line:10%
And what if God instead
had lipstick because God

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:24.330 align:middle line:10%
was a woman.

00:03:24.330 --> 00:03:26.250 align:middle line:10%
But in reality,
you can't see God.

00:03:26.250 --> 00:03:28.050 align:middle line:10%
We can only experience God.

00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:30.570 align:middle line:84%
We experience God in
the beautiful sunrises

00:03:30.570 --> 00:03:33.800 align:middle line:84%
in the Phoenix
Valley, or the sunsets

00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:36.620 align:middle line:84%
along the Western
shores of Hawaii,

00:03:36.620 --> 00:03:38.160 align:middle line:84%
in the multicolored
beautiful faces

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.710 align:middle line:84%
of the people that walk along
the crowded streets of downtown

00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:44.760 align:middle line:84%
New York, or London, or
Rome, or San Francisco.

00:03:44.760 --> 00:03:47.130 align:middle line:84%
So in reality, we only
can experience God.

00:03:47.130 --> 00:03:49.260 align:middle line:84%
And everything that we
feel and hear that's good,

00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:51.200 align:middle line:84%
rather than actually
have an image

00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:53.130 align:middle line:90%
of a physical person as God.

00:03:53.130 --> 00:03:56.080 align:middle line:84%
>> I'd love to hear you
speak more about the people

00:03:56.080 --> 00:03:57.960 align:middle line:90%
at the Whole Life expos.

00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:00.480 align:middle line:84%
Because you could lecture
all over the place

00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:02.010 align:middle line:90%
if you wanted to.

00:04:02.010 --> 00:04:03.270 align:middle line:90%
And yet, you're here.

00:04:03.270 --> 00:04:07.800 align:middle line:84%
And the audience here
is fascinated with you.

00:04:07.800 --> 00:04:09.900 align:middle line:84%
What do you get when you
come to Whole Life Expo?

00:04:09.900 --> 00:04:12.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, first of all, I think
it starts with the people who

00:04:12.420 --> 00:04:15.160 align:middle line:84%
represent Whole Life
Expo, the staff.

00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And there's a genuine
love, and friendship,

00:04:20.050 --> 00:04:23.130 align:middle line:84%
and wanting to share the
spirituality that we all

00:04:23.130 --> 00:04:25.470 align:middle line:84%
have inside of us with people
all around the country.

00:04:25.470 --> 00:04:27.850 align:middle line:10%
So this, to me,
is very important.

00:04:27.850 --> 00:04:30.510 align:middle line:10%
And I feel that when I'm working
with the Whole Life Expo.

00:04:30.510 --> 00:04:32.730 align:middle line:10%
And that's why I've chosen
Whole Life, as opposed

00:04:32.730 --> 00:04:33.930 align:middle line:10%
to other expos.

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:35.610 align:middle line:10%
But also the audiences.

00:04:35.610 --> 00:04:37.350 align:middle line:84%
The audiences truly
are an audience

00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:39.507 align:middle line:84%
that are coming to
want to understand

00:04:39.507 --> 00:04:41.590 align:middle line:84%
their relationship with
God, as well as to enhance

00:04:41.590 --> 00:04:42.828 align:middle line:90%
their own spirituality.

00:04:42.828 --> 00:04:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
commitment, I believe,

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:48.870 align:middle line:84%
that Whole Life Expo, as
well as myself has made.

00:04:48.870 --> 00:04:52.270 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to talk a little bit
about your creative process.

00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:56.010 align:middle line:84%
Now, I talked to you a long
time ago about "The Messengers."

00:04:56.010 --> 00:05:00.667 align:middle line:84%
And it was fascinating,
because you were not

00:05:00.667 --> 00:05:01.750 align:middle line:90%
writing it from your head.

00:05:01.750 --> 00:05:06.250 align:middle line:84%
It was somebody else speaking to
you, and through you, and even

00:05:06.250 --> 00:05:07.870 align:middle line:90%
through your arms you wrote.

00:05:07.870 --> 00:05:09.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:05:09.970 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Did the same thing happen
with "In God's Truth?"

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:13.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:13.090 --> 00:05:14.860 align:middle line:90%
It's interesting.

00:05:14.860 --> 00:05:17.810 align:middle line:84%
I wrote "In God's Truth"
in longhand with a pen.

00:05:17.810 --> 00:05:18.865 align:middle line:90%
>> You did?

00:05:18.865 --> 00:05:19.990 align:middle line:90%
How time consuming is that?

00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:22.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I found that it was
totally different when I tried

00:05:22.600 --> 00:05:25.390 align:middle line:84%
to dictate on a tape
machine, or on a computer.

00:05:25.390 --> 00:05:27.490 align:middle line:84%
I was getting totally
different information.

00:05:27.490 --> 00:05:29.350 align:middle line:10%
And I truly believed
that I could

00:05:29.350 --> 00:05:32.320 align:middle line:10%
feel the energy changing with
every chapter I was writing.

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:34.180 align:middle line:10%
And oftentimes, I wasn't
even aware of what

00:05:34.180 --> 00:05:35.600 align:middle line:10%
I was going to write next.

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:38.140 align:middle line:84%
And I'd find myself saying,
wow, did I write that?

00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:39.160 align:middle line:90%
There's poetry in it.

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:40.390 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not a poet.

00:05:40.390 --> 00:05:42.377 align:middle line:84%
And some of the poetry
is beautiful poetry.

00:05:42.377 --> 00:05:43.960 align:middle line:84%
And I don't even
know when I wrote it.

00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:47.170 align:middle line:84%
I found it in a drawer with my
handwriting on a piece of paper

00:05:47.170 --> 00:05:49.520 align:middle line:84%
with my pen and didn't
have a date on it.

00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:52.300 align:middle line:84%
So I honestly believe that I
got a tremendous number of help

00:05:52.300 --> 00:05:54.390 align:middle line:84%
from a number of
different co-authors

00:05:54.390 --> 00:05:55.570 align:middle line:90%
in different chapters.

00:05:55.570 --> 00:05:57.997 align:middle line:10%
>> So then it wasn't a
situation where you would get up

00:05:57.997 --> 00:06:00.080 align:middle line:10%
in the morning, and have
a cup of coffee, and say,

00:06:00.080 --> 00:06:01.720 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to write
from 9:00 to 1:00?

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:06:03.340 --> 00:06:07.950 align:middle line:84%
I found that I could
literally put myself

00:06:07.950 --> 00:06:10.215 align:middle line:84%
in a position of
privacy, whether it

00:06:10.215 --> 00:06:13.680 align:middle line:84%
was in my home or my office,
and focus my attention,

00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:16.080 align:middle line:84%
and write an entire
chapter, almost

00:06:16.080 --> 00:06:18.880 align:middle line:84%
without requiring any changes
within a period of 20,

00:06:18.880 --> 00:06:20.010 align:middle line:90%
25 minutes.

00:06:20.010 --> 00:06:22.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And your publisher
wouldn't say, OK, Nick,

00:06:22.170 --> 00:06:22.640 align:middle line:90%
this didn't work?

00:06:22.640 --> 00:06:23.440 align:middle line:90%
This sentence.

00:06:23.440 --> 00:06:25.142 align:middle line:90%
It was just as it was?

00:06:25.142 --> 00:06:27.600 align:middle line:84%
>> There were no changes made
in publishing other than some

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:28.950 align:middle line:90%
grammar.

00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:32.217 align:middle line:84%
But there were no changes as
far as the messages that we're

00:06:32.217 --> 00:06:34.050 align:middle line:84%
trying to convey or the
manner in which they

00:06:34.050 --> 00:06:36.570 align:middle line:90%
were being conveyed.

00:06:36.570 --> 00:06:41.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you hear the beginnings
of other ideas rattling around

00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:41.910 align:middle line:90%
in your head?

00:06:41.910 --> 00:06:44.070 align:middle line:84%
Like when you complete a
book, when you completed

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:45.750 align:middle line:84%
"The Messengers,"
certainly there must

00:06:45.750 --> 00:06:50.175 align:middle line:84%
have been something that
said, there's more to tell.

00:06:50.175 --> 00:06:52.050 align:middle line:84%
>> It's true that when
I finished writing "In

00:06:52.050 --> 00:06:54.990 align:middle line:84%
God's Truth," there were still
some additional things I wanted

00:06:54.990 --> 00:06:56.220 align:middle line:90%
to say.

00:06:56.220 --> 00:07:00.820 align:middle line:84%
But what I got, literally,
was the message from spirit,

00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:01.620 align:middle line:90%
saying, no, Nick.

00:07:01.620 --> 00:07:02.440 align:middle line:90%
Not now.

00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:04.263 align:middle line:84%
There are some
incredible experiences

00:07:04.263 --> 00:07:06.180 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
over the next few months.

00:07:06.180 --> 00:07:07.720 align:middle line:84%
And wait til you've
had those experiences.

00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.053 align:middle line:84%
And then you'll know you're
ready to write another book.

00:07:10.053 --> 00:07:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>> So often I think
not the answers,

00:07:13.170 --> 00:07:18.670 align:middle line:84%
but the questions are what tell
us a great deal about people

00:07:18.670 --> 00:07:19.470 align:middle line:90%
these days.

00:07:19.470 --> 00:07:22.380 align:middle line:90%


00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:25.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm curious as to the
questions that people ask you,

00:07:25.950 --> 00:07:28.680 align:middle line:90%
like after you lecture.

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:30.510 align:middle line:90%
What do people want to know?

00:07:30.510 --> 00:07:33.180 align:middle line:84%
>> The thing that I found--
and I didn't anticipate this.

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:36.618 align:middle line:10%
I did not realize this when
I first made the commitment

00:07:36.618 --> 00:07:38.660 align:middle line:10%
to cross that threshold
and do what I'm doing now

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:42.840 align:middle line:10%
my life is the tremendous
number of people

00:07:42.840 --> 00:07:45.330 align:middle line:10%
who are searching
for and understanding

00:07:45.330 --> 00:07:47.640 align:middle line:10%
their relationship with
God who at one time

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:51.510 align:middle line:10%
were involved in a religion
and fell out of their religion

00:07:51.510 --> 00:07:55.080 align:middle line:10%
because they could not take, any
longer, perhaps the punishing

00:07:55.080 --> 00:08:01.730 align:middle line:10%
God perspective, a place
called hell, guilt and sin.

00:08:01.730 --> 00:08:03.980 align:middle line:84%
And what I find, many people
come up to me afterwards.

00:08:03.980 --> 00:08:06.060 align:middle line:84%
Or we receive over
200 letters a week

00:08:06.060 --> 00:08:09.270 align:middle line:84%
in our office saying, thank
you for bringing me back

00:08:09.270 --> 00:08:11.552 align:middle line:84%
to a relationship with
God because of one

00:08:11.552 --> 00:08:14.010 align:middle line:84%
that they had lost earlier in
their life because of the way

00:08:14.010 --> 00:08:17.490 align:middle line:90%
God was being presented to them.

00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:21.510 align:middle line:10%
>> Had you had a relationship
with God and then lost

00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:26.650 align:middle line:10%
a relationship at any point in
your life, like in your youth?

00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:32.553 align:middle line:84%
I'm curious as to your path,
how you found your way here.

00:08:32.553 --> 00:08:34.720 align:middle line:84%
>> I went through a very
long period of time where I

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:36.640 align:middle line:90%
didn't have religion.

00:08:36.640 --> 00:08:38.988 align:middle line:10%
And I still don't have one now.

00:08:38.988 --> 00:08:41.530 align:middle line:10%
But what I always had in my life
was a spiritual relationship

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:42.520 align:middle line:10%
with God.

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:46.930 align:middle line:10%
And there was a time when I
literally asked my guides, what

00:08:46.930 --> 00:08:49.820 align:middle line:10%
I call the messengers of God,
how come you've chosen me

00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:50.620 align:middle line:10%
for my mission.

00:08:50.620 --> 00:08:52.030 align:middle line:90%
I don't even have a religion.

00:08:52.030 --> 00:08:53.830 align:middle line:84%
And their response was,
well, Nick, what religion

00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:54.663 align:middle line:90%
do you think God is?

00:08:54.663 --> 00:08:57.340 align:middle line:84%
Do you think God is a
Mennonite, a Quaker, a Mormon?

00:08:57.340 --> 00:08:59.200 align:middle line:84%
God doesn't have
a religion either,

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.100 align:middle line:84%
but embraces all
of his children,

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:03.310 align:middle line:84%
and gives all of his
children his love.

00:09:03.310 --> 00:09:05.950 align:middle line:84%
So I think there's
something beyond religion.

00:09:05.950 --> 00:09:09.760 align:middle line:84%
If you think of religion as a
series of different buildings,

00:09:09.760 --> 00:09:11.710 align:middle line:90%
beyond religion is a thread.

00:09:11.710 --> 00:09:14.260 align:middle line:84%
There's threads that come out
of those buildings that connect

00:09:14.260 --> 00:09:16.450 align:middle line:90%
them with your spirituality.

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:18.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you so much, Nick.

00:09:18.970 --> 00:09:21.670 align:middle line:84%
Every time I talk to you
I have a greater insight

00:09:21.670 --> 00:09:23.803 align:middle line:90%
into my life and my God.

00:09:23.803 --> 00:09:25.220 align:middle line:84%
So I thank you
very much for that.

00:09:25.220 --> 00:09:27.012 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I really
appreciate that, Chantal.

00:09:27.012 --> 00:09:29.135 align:middle line:84%
But I recognize, it's
not me that's important.

00:09:29.135 --> 00:09:31.010 align:middle line:84%
It's the messages that
you and I are sharing.

