00:19:13.080 --> 00:19:15.160 align:middle line:84%
Nature never settles
down and says,

00:19:15.160 --> 00:19:17.010 align:middle line:84%
I think I'll skip the
seasons for two years.

00:19:17.010 --> 00:19:19.230 align:middle line:90%
Everything's always changing.

00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:21.780 align:middle line:84%
So we are always, if
we're in our natural mode,

00:19:21.780 --> 00:19:24.700 align:middle line:84%
we are going to always change
if we have the courage to do it.

00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:27.750 align:middle line:84%
So I went to him going, my god,
everything's upheaved again.

00:19:27.750 --> 00:19:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Barbara, when
you came into this life,

00:19:31.350 --> 00:19:34.690 align:middle line:84%
in the box that said, check
the kind of life you want,

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:36.330 align:middle line:90%
you didn't check stability.

00:19:36.330 --> 00:19:38.657 align:middle line:90%
You checked growth.

00:19:38.657 --> 00:19:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And I knew when he
said it that I had.

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:41.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:41.040 --> 00:19:42.650 align:middle line:90%
>> I had checked growth.

00:19:42.650 --> 00:19:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And growth and stability
are at odds with each other.

00:19:46.430 --> 00:19:49.400 align:middle line:84%
Because when there is
change, and growth is change,

00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:51.690 align:middle line:90%
that means what was has to die.

00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:52.610 align:middle line:90%
It has to transform.

00:19:52.610 --> 00:19:53.410 align:middle line:90%
So yeah.

00:19:53.410 --> 00:19:56.120 align:middle line:84%
Your friends who aren't into
anything new age, everyone

00:19:56.120 --> 00:19:58.683 align:middle line:84%
who's watching, may look
like they're happier.

00:19:58.683 --> 00:20:01.100 align:middle line:84%
You may even be embarrassed
to say to them, read this book

00:20:01.100 --> 00:20:02.017 align:middle line:90%
or take this workshop.

00:20:02.017 --> 00:20:04.880 align:middle line:84%
Cause they're thinking, hey,
your life doesn't look too hot.

00:20:04.880 --> 00:20:05.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:05.280 --> 00:20:06.080 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:10.070 align:middle line:10%
>> So we have to really
not judge ourselves by what

00:20:10.070 --> 00:20:12.440 align:middle line:10%
our life looks like
on the outside,

00:20:12.440 --> 00:20:15.560 align:middle line:10%
but by what we're feeling
like, how we're growing,

00:20:15.560 --> 00:20:16.910 align:middle line:10%
how we're learning.

00:20:16.910 --> 00:20:18.710 align:middle line:84%
Am I becoming a more
loving human being?

00:20:18.710 --> 00:20:21.230 align:middle line:84%
Am I becoming a more
wise human being?

00:20:21.230 --> 00:20:26.570 align:middle line:84%
Not is my life looking the same
way today as it did yesterday?

00:20:26.570 --> 00:20:29.180 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that
strikes so many people about

00:20:29.180 --> 00:20:33.290 align:middle line:84%
you is that in your lectures,
without that going into any

00:20:33.290 --> 00:20:36.720 align:middle line:84%
great detail, you are so
honest about your own life.

00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:38.310 align:middle line:90%
>> I spill the beans.

00:20:38.310 --> 00:20:39.110 align:middle line:90%
>> You do.

00:20:39.110 --> 00:20:40.700 align:middle line:10%
You spill the beans, Barbara.

00:20:40.700 --> 00:20:42.920 align:middle line:90%
And it's so authentic.

00:20:42.920 --> 00:20:45.200 align:middle line:90%
It's so appealing.

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:49.920 align:middle line:10%
Do you ever leave a workshop and
think, oh, man, I went too far?

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:50.720 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:20:50.720 --> 00:20:52.790 align:middle line:90%
I don't think I went too far.

00:20:52.790 --> 00:20:53.850 align:middle line:90%
>> That's great.

00:20:53.850 --> 00:20:55.100 align:middle line:90%
>> You know, it's interesting.

00:20:55.100 --> 00:21:00.080 align:middle line:84%
I grew up watching
a lot of teachers

00:21:00.080 --> 00:21:07.495 align:middle line:84%
who put themselves on pedestals,
who appeared to be perfect.

00:21:07.495 --> 00:21:09.620 align:middle line:84%
What I learned from that
was that it didn't give me

00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:10.760 align:middle line:90%
room to be imperfect.

00:21:10.760 --> 00:21:12.200 align:middle line:90%
It didn't give me room to grow.

00:21:12.200 --> 00:21:13.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:13.160 --> 00:21:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And not as a device, but as
a way of keeping myself honest,

00:21:18.890 --> 00:21:21.710 align:middle line:84%
I decided a long time ago to
share my process with people.

00:21:21.710 --> 00:21:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And my process
has been dramatic.

00:21:24.530 --> 00:21:26.970 align:middle line:90%
It's been different.

00:21:26.970 --> 00:21:27.890 align:middle line:90%
It's been eventful.

00:21:27.890 --> 00:21:28.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:28.690 --> 00:21:33.200 align:middle line:90%
>> And for a reason.

00:21:33.200 --> 00:21:35.090 align:middle line:84%
I think when we
choose to be teachers,

00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:37.400 align:middle line:84%
and I mean consciously
choose before we

00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:39.770 align:middle line:84%
come into a life
to be teachers, we

00:21:39.770 --> 00:21:42.678 align:middle line:90%
take on a certain kind of karma.

00:21:42.678 --> 00:21:44.720 align:middle line:84%
I bet you some of the
people you've interviewed--

00:21:44.720 --> 00:21:47.780 align:middle line:84%
and I've talked to many of
them, cause they're my friends--

00:21:47.780 --> 00:21:52.030 align:middle line:84%
we, behind the scenes, agree
that most teachers did not

00:21:52.030 --> 00:21:53.655 align:middle line:84%
meet their high school
sweetheart at 19

00:21:53.655 --> 00:21:55.862 align:middle line:84%
and have lived for 40
years happily ever after.

00:21:55.862 --> 00:21:56.820 align:middle line:90%
>> I certainly did not.

00:21:56.820 --> 00:21:57.830 align:middle line:90%
>> They have had lives.

00:21:57.830 --> 00:21:59.540 align:middle line:90%
They have had stuff.

00:21:59.540 --> 00:22:01.430 align:middle line:90%
Because that's what's molded us.

00:22:01.430 --> 00:22:02.690 align:middle line:90%
That's the fire.

00:22:02.690 --> 00:22:04.310 align:middle line:84%
That's what's
given us and taught

00:22:04.310 --> 00:22:06.600 align:middle line:90%
us compassion for other people.

00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:08.840 align:middle line:84%
I've been through
so much in my life.

00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:10.940 align:middle line:84%
Very few things anyone
could ever tell me

00:22:10.940 --> 00:22:12.770 align:middle line:90%
I haven't experienced myself.

00:22:12.770 --> 00:22:15.440 align:middle line:84%
What that's taught
me is compassion.

00:22:15.440 --> 00:22:17.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't judge people
when I hear them.

00:22:17.390 --> 00:22:19.710 align:middle line:84%
I don't think, well,
I've been this.

00:22:19.710 --> 00:22:21.620 align:middle line:84%
So I don't understand
what your problem is.

00:22:21.620 --> 00:22:23.370 align:middle line:84%
And I think people
really appreciate that.

00:22:23.370 --> 00:22:25.280 align:middle line:84%
That's the one
comment I always hear

00:22:25.280 --> 00:22:29.480 align:middle line:84%
from people, which is your
honesty gives me permission

00:22:29.480 --> 00:22:32.850 align:middle line:84%
to love myself, no matter
what I'm going through.

00:22:32.850 --> 00:22:36.305 align:middle line:84%
So people will
challenge me, saying,

00:22:36.305 --> 00:22:38.180 align:middle line:84%
what gives you the right
to teach about this?

00:22:38.180 --> 00:22:40.222 align:middle line:84%
You've been married and
divorced all these times.

00:22:40.222 --> 00:22:43.220 align:middle line:84%
And I'll say, that's
exactly my credential.

00:22:43.220 --> 00:22:44.420 align:middle line:90%
That's my credential.

00:22:44.420 --> 00:22:45.650 align:middle line:90%
That's what I've taken on.

00:22:45.650 --> 00:22:49.400 align:middle line:84%
That's my sacrifice,
that I have taken on.

00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:51.530 align:middle line:84%
Let me have as many
experiences as possible.

00:22:51.530 --> 00:22:53.450 align:middle line:84%
Let me go through
as much as possible.

00:22:53.450 --> 00:22:55.160 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm not just
here for myself.

00:22:55.160 --> 00:22:56.498 align:middle line:90%
I'm here to teach.

00:22:56.498 --> 00:22:57.540 align:middle line:90%
>> I know you have to go.

00:22:57.540 --> 00:22:59.390 align:middle line:84%
But I do want to
say to you, I thank

00:22:59.390 --> 00:23:03.920 align:middle line:84%
you so much for sitting down
and chatting with us here

00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:04.970 align:middle line:90%
at Wisdom.

00:23:04.970 --> 00:23:07.880 align:middle line:84%
And having known you
for all these years,

00:23:07.880 --> 00:23:10.850 align:middle line:84%
it's very gratifying to me
to see that you are still,

00:23:10.850 --> 00:23:13.850 align:middle line:84%
from the first day I met
you, as much a truth seeker

00:23:13.850 --> 00:23:15.780 align:middle line:90%
as you are a truth teller.

00:23:15.780 --> 00:23:16.580 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Barbara.

00:23:16.580 --> 00:23:18.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

